The wyrm goes by many names. Ansur. The Waiting Storm. The Heart of the Gate.
The Blade of Avernus!
It is exactly what I think.

EditorData.NodeContext: A bit of hurt, a bit of anger, but always composed.

Text.Value: This is no ordinary dragon.
It's time you two made up. We've got a city to save.
I tried, but she refused to leave. She's lost all hope.
No. My son -

EditorData.NodeContext: Beginning to see the truth. Your son became a devil to save your life.

Text.Value: Wouldn't you rather wake the dragon yourself?
I'll seek the wyrm and ask for his help.
I trust you, Wyll. Follow your heart, wherever it leads.
Glad to see you, friend.
Baldur's Gate stands on the brink of the abyss. My father was clear: we awaken the wyrm, and take back the city.
Will the people even accept me as duke? I mean, look at me.
The Blade of Frontiers is dead. I will be Wyll Ravengard, proud Duke of Baldur's Gate.
You sold your soul to save Baldur's Gate - and I cast you out for it.
Thank you.
Your faith in Wyll is well-founded. We will seek the wyrm and ask for his help.
May the Triad guide you.
Please - promise that you'll be the shield that defends, the sword that slays, and the hammer that rebuilds. Be our champion.

EditorData.stateContext: Wyll and Ravengard touch their own heads in mind meld

Text.Value: Everything I did, I did for Baldur's Gate. I did for you.
Ansur was a myth, father. It is up to me to save Baldur's Gate from the Absolute.

EditorData.logicalname: Wyll is already Blade of Avernus

Text.Value: Let the Emperor reveal your memories.
Go. You must awaken the wyrm.
You want my gratitude? Fine - take your fill. But I will not celebrate this infernal resurrection.

EditorData.NodeContext: A bit of hurt, a bit of anger, but always composed.

Text.Value: It isn't what you think. It never was.
Tell Ravengard about the battle with Ansur.
I am now the Blade of Avernus.

EditorData.NodeContext: Confident, but not heightened, just humble, Not too high on his own heroism.

Text.Value: *Ravengard's tadpole clenches as your memories - and Wyll's - flow into him.*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Mind meld. Ravengard, Wyll, and players touch their own heads.

Text.Value: As you wish.
Then go with my blessing. Be Faerûn's great defender.
Returning from Elturel, I discovered the plans of the Absolutists. I immediately realised the city couldn't defend itself against such an army.
In Ansur's defeat, I've found my spirit renewed. Once I've vanquished the Absolute, I will walk in your footsteps and lead the city as a Grand Duke.

EditorData.logicalname: OOM, has Wyrmway quest, defeated Ansur

Text.Value: Everything I did, I did for Baldur's Gate. I did for you.

EditorData.NodeContext: Quietly

Text.Value: It wasn't the heat that woke me - it was the scent. Cultists had set fire to the place. I don't remember being taken, just the smoke burning my throat before I fell.
Say nothing.
*Ravengard sees Mizora and her infernal sisters. He sees the agony in your face as an impossible choice is set before you.*
Hail, hail, and hail again.
*And he sees everything beyond. The nautiloid journey, the perilous path to Moonrise, the Astral Prism, and the Emperor within.*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: The mind meld ends after the node is over.

Text.Value: - my duty is first and foremost to the city and its people. There's something I must ask of you.
*A calm settles over you. The elder brain is a menace - but you are the Blade of Avernus. No abomination is too powerful for you to overcome.*
W-Wyll? It - it can't be. By Balduran's graces, have you fallen so far that Avernus has taken you?

EditorData.logicalname: (Note: In this path, Wyll always has to be in devil form)

Text.Value: I once held a copy, but it was stolen. Find it, let it set the path before you.
Baldur's Gate stands on the brink of the abyss. It is clear: we awaken the wyrm, and take back the city.
I am Wyll Ravengard, son of Ulder!
Father, please - there's something I must show you.
Wyll's devoted his life to protecting the Coast. He's used his power wisely.
I am the defender of the weak, I am the stalker of devils -
Waking a dragon doesn't sound like a good idea.
The Blade of Frontiers is no more. I will be Wyll Ravengard, son of Ulder, proud Duke of Baldur's Gate.

EditorData.NodeContext: Confident, but not heightened, just humble, Not too high on his own heroism.

Text.Value: She stood by me even as the Hells' fires lapped at my feet. You must free her.
My own son, still the she-devil's toy. Is this my fate - to rise from death into a hell of my own boy's making?

EditorData.NodeContext: A bit of hurt, a bit of anger, but always composed.

Text.Value: What was your business in Elturel?
*The past becomes present, and Wyll's thoughts are laid bare. Ravengard sees Wyll partnering with Mizora to defeat Tiamat's cultists before they could lay siege to Baldur's Gate.*
You are a better man than most, and a better son than I deserve. I'll yet make amends, but -
You are a hero, not an aristocrat. The Blade is a champion. 'Duke Wyll Ravengard' is not.
No. And I'm not about to.
My friend, I -

EditorData.NodeContext: Overcome by a headache.

Text.Value: Today, you've earned my trust. I know you will do right by me when the time comes.
I was forbidden to tell you before. But now, I can tell you the truth.
It is exactly what I think.

EditorData.NodeContext: A bit of hurt, a bit of anger, but always composed.

Synopsis: Default Ravengard dialogue. Depending on the path, Ravengard may urge you to save the city, and if Wyll is in party, will offer the quest to go to the Wyrmway. Wyll's endgame state is detremined here: He may become a Duke, the Blade of Avernus, or remain the Blade of Frontiers
